<subSubSection id="48D355CA8ECCFF4248A75669FE0CFD35" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418ECCFF4248A75669FEBCFD51" blockId="130.[151,1436,325,890]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538ECCFF4248A75669FE2EFEAD" bold="true" box="[151,395,325,350]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48ECCFF424ABA5669FCB1FEAD" box="[650,788,325,349]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" unit="mm" value="1.7999999999999998" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.7">1.7–1.9 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown, except segment 1 testaceous; mesosoma and metasoma black; legs brown, except tibiae and tarsi testaceous. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 9:5:6:7.5:8:7:6.5:7:5.5:10. Head dull, granulated; frontal line complete, but very slight; POL = 6; OL = 2.5; OOL = 4; OPL = 2.5; TL = 4; occipital carina complete. Scutum shiny, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.2 length of scutum. Scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with strong transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels and median area as rugose as lateral areas. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein shorter than proximal part (2:7). Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48ECCFF424AB75549FD5DFD8D" box="[647,760,613,637]" captionStart="PLATE 33" captionStartId="126.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,219,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-98@126.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="PLATE 33. A, B, F. Chelae, holotypes. C–E. Male genitalia, holotypes. A. Anteon laotianum (from Olmi 1984). B. A. lesagei (from Olmi 1998e). C. A. lini (from Olmi 1996c). D. A. luzonense (from Olmi 1991). E. A. maculatum (from Xu et al. 2001a). F. A. liui (from Xu et al. 2010a). Scale bar 0.40 mm for A, 0.30 mm for B, 0.18 mm for C and D, 0.14 mm for E and 0.31 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278492" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278492/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Plate 33D</figureCitation>
) about as long as penis, without distal inner process. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ECCFF4248F75581FE0CFD35" blockId="130.[151,1436,325,890]" box="[199,425,685,709]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538ECCFF4248F75581FE80FD35" bold="true" box="[199,293,685,709]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
